				</div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Hepatitis B and C: Viruses that attack the liver cause these forms of hepatitis. Hepatitis is the most common disease transmitted by blood transfusions. According to the American Red Cross, <b>about one blood transfusion in 205,000 transmits a hepatitis B infection, and one blood transfusion in 1,935,000 transmits hepatitis C</b>. In most cases there are no symptoms, but hepatitis can lead to liver failure and other problems.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
